cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use QuickScan in your work, please cite it as below."
title: QuickScan
abstract: >-
  QuickScan is a single-file, browser-based optical mark recognition (OMR)
  bubble-sheet grader — a no-server, no-hardware replacement for physical
  Scantron machines. An instructor prints answer sheets, students fill them in
  by hand, and the instructor scans them to PDF and uploads them; QuickScan
  grades every sheet client-side with canvas-based OMR and reports per-student
  scores and grades, a score histogram, item analysis (per-question percent
  correct and discrimination index), KR-20 / Cronbach's alpha reliability,
  z-scores, distractor analysis, grade curving, and a downloadable
  self-contained HTML report.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Díaz"
    given-names: "Fernando"
    affiliation: "West Texas A&M University"
    email: "ferdiazfer@gmail.com"
